cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robot-assisted feeding and developing manipulation strategies for bite acquisition. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes using online learning to learn from failures and improve the robot's performance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes variants of contextual bandit algorithms to minimize cumulative regret. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) may be relevant if the robot uses visual information to identify and manipulate food items. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the goal of successful feeding, which involves interaction between the robot and the human being fed.
